1. In this schedule— 

“B1” means the numerical value which when expressed as a percentage 
represents the rate at which base year qualifying income of €1 to €1,000,000 is 
to be levied, as contemplated in the template; 

“B2” means the numerical value which when expressed as a percentage 
represents the rate at which the base year qualifying income is to be levied, as 
contemplated in the formula in paragraph 14; 

“base year” means the calendar year of 1 January 2023 to 31 December 2023 or, 
where a television programme service provider has been in operation for part 
only of that calendar year, such part of that calendar year; 

“base year qualifying income” means the qualifying income of a television 
programme service provider in the base year; 

“community broadcaster” means a person holding a contract under section 72 of 
the Act of 2009; 

“complete table” means the table referred to in paragraph 8; 

“costs” includes the Commission’s working capital requirements; 

“L1” means, in respect of each television programme service provider, the 
monetary value which will result from the application of the template; 

“L2” means, in respect of each television programme service provider, the 
monetary value which will result from the calculation at paragraph 13; 

“levy” means the levy calculated in accordance with this schedule 2; 

“levy payer” means a television programme service provider who must pay a 
levy; 

“sector” means the sector comprising of the total number of television 
programme service providers; 

“television programme service provider” means a provider of a service which 
comprises a compilation of audio-visual programme material of any description 
and is transmitted, distributed or relayed by means of wireless telegraphy 
directly or indirectly for reception by the general public; and 

“template” means the table set out in paragraph 8.

1. 

In this schedule— 

“C” means the numerical value which when expressed as a percentage represents 
the rate at which the base year qualifying income is to be levied, as contemplated 
in the formula; 

“base year” means the calendar year of 1 January 2023 to 31 December 2023 or, 
where a sound broadcasting service provider has been in operation for part only 
of that calendar year, such part of that calendar year; 

“base year qualifying income” means the qualifying income of sound 
broadcasting providers in the base year; 

“community broadcaster” means a person holding a contract under sections 64 
or 68(1)(b) of the Act of 2009; 

“costs” includes the Commission’s working capital requirements; 

“formula” means the formula set out in paragraph 7; 

“institutional broadcaster” means a person holding a contract under section 68(2) 
of the Act of 2009; 

“levy” means the levy calculated in accordance with this schedule; 

“levy payer” means a sound broadcasting service provider who must pay a levy; 

“sector” means the sector comprising of the total number of sound broadcasting 
service providers; 

"sound broadcasting service provider” means a provider of a service, within the 
meaning of Articles 56 and 57 of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European 
Union, where— 

(a) 

(b) 

the principal purpose of the service is devoted to providing sound 
programmes, by electronic communications networks, to the 
general public, under its own editorial responsibility, in order to 
inform, entertain or educate, and 

the service is provided for simultaneous or near-simultaneous 
listening to sound programmes on the basis of a programme 
schedule; 

 “temporary broadcaster” means a person holding a contract under section 
68(1)(a) of the Act of 2009.

1. 

In this schedule— 

“audiovisual on-demand media service provider” means a provider of 
audiovisual on-demand media services; 

“base year” means the calendar year of 1 January 2023 to 31 December 2023 or, 
where an audiovisual on-demand service provider has been in operation for part 
only of that calendar year, such part of that calendar year; 

“base year qualifying income” means the qualifying income of an audiovisual 
on-demand media services provider in the base year; 

“costs” includes the Commission’s working capital requirements; 

“D” means the numerical value which when expressed as a percentage represents 
the rate at which the base year qualifying income is to be levied, as contemplated 
in the formula; 

“formula” means the formula set out in paragraph 5; and 

"sector” means the sector comprising the total number of audiovisual on-demand 
media service providers.

1. In this schedule— 

“broadcasting funding scheme” means a scheme administered by the 
Commission by virtue of Part 10 of the Act of 2009; 

“Government” means the Government provided for in Bunreacht na hÉireann; 

“interactive income” means income generated by a provider from listener or 
viewer response to a broadcast including, without limitation, telephony income 
and income from online payments which are so generated; 

“non-linear service” means a service provided by a television programme 
service provider whereby a person may view or listen to programmes at the 
moment chosen by the user and at his or her individual request on the basis of 
a catalogue of programmes selected by the television programme service 
provider; 

“public body” means an entity whose decisions are subject to judicial review; 
and 

“provider” means each provider of services set out in this Schedule whose levy 
shall be determined based on qualifying income.

